y_name":"Rasty","avatar_url":"https://i.imgur.com/MOu1yIH.jpg","count":1},{"fid":4395,"username":"loracle","display_name":"üîÆ","avatar_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/BCnrCATZYzC-ZqEkBCeOrkSgN1COirrtkTD32f5CREVnbeRgBDztBrNTNWLaqhIIZ7W66knz1p7Gnh0jw4s6ThwszTkvfYIbFwKFiQ","count":1},{"fid":4564,"username":"kevinoconnell","display_name":"Kevin","avatar_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/x6wugf4yKxyx9kDw0vGgjJWOoFr81nSzstx4ANW_ijb2W2pWPQP3ORf0_4YE7ZDnP9kKFxevVTVbe9sG5LGe-Dl1ToeQ3rmDPSf5Bg","count":1},{"fid":4698,"username":"jenna","display_name":"»∑ƒèùêõùêõüå≥","avatar_url":"https://i.seadn.io/gae/gGMb9VRmeQXvHehApvMymBYVz99JDtUkJNgfUaKH12bslu4vNtPoVGg1i1fnAmjJe3pHQENIjZaMC8caBWvP17B99DUaAwyRMnh0?w=500&auto=format","count":1}]},"emojis_view":{"emojis":[]},"top_casts_view":{"top_casts":[{"text":"Currently working on a program to convert ebooks to a single HTML file, because I really prefer to use my browser and have normal scroll behavior. base64-encoding all the images like SingleFile was pretty easy; the harder part is fixing all the parts of Calibre‚Äôs CSS that impair reading. https://i.imgur.com/HdWpAsD.jpg","thread_hash":"0x5fb31440f7a81bb4afc5146bce7ea6bbb2ea870ef162772c8298f6f05d21bcfd","hash":"0x5fb31440f7a81bb4afc5146bce7ea6bbb2ea870ef162772c8298f6f05d21bcfd","likes":7,"replies":0,"recasts":1},{"text":"I am pleased to announce unbook, which solves the DRM-free .{epub, mobi, azw3, ...} ebook reading problem by converting the book to a self-contained HTML file with all the images inlined using data: URIs. You can now just read everything in your browser.\n\nhttps://unbook.ludios.org https://i.imgur.com/uftndd3.jpg","thread_hash":"0xb1460bc592daf85c2e7a2c6ffd5b59222f0e837fe0bc3c98519a26a9aa6e0e09","hash":"0xb1460bc592daf85c2e7a2c6ffd5b59222f0e837fe0bc3c98519a26a9aa6e0e09","likes":5,"replies":1,"recasts":1},{"text":"TIL iOS Farcaster silently fails to attach PNG images with an indexed color palette","thread_hash":"0x92103cd6b1f9dde05c680181276c26f7b8996e06ddbc6639a13498e483cdd787","hash":"0x92103cd6b1f9dde05c680181276c26f7b8996e06ddbc6639a13498e483cdd787","likes":2,"replies":0,"recasts":1},{"text":"Stanis≈Çaw Lem‚Äôs _Solaris_\nDavid McCullough‚Äôs _The Wright Brothers_\nWilliam Langewiesche‚Äôs _The Outlaw Sea_\nElif Batuman‚Äôs _The Idiot_\nHamilton Helmer‚Äôs _7 Powers_","thread_hash":"0xbcf26d5b97b5b28357b136c4d0384b4e4e9822f2553ba2665f5c0739c693f517","hash":"0xd35f827017daf6438cc47fa4776cb691aebc38ed0452e8add92910dedaf468ff","likes":1,"replies":0,"recasts":0},{"text":"unbook was created after I repeatedly noticed that I had a better reading experience with Calibre's HTMLZ output in Chrome or iOS Safari than with any ebook reader software. Such programs often have peculiar UX issues which are not always outweighed by whatever benefits they offer.","thread_hash":"0xb1460bc592daf85c2e7a2c6ffd5b59222f0e837fe0bc3c98519a26a9aa6e0e09","hash":"0xb8326b4d410b351523055a2cde1ef378cc09f1d36e830bfcd1933b0be19e0eb3","likes":0,"replies":1,"recasts":0},{"text":"But HTMLZ output was created for editing, not for reading (in 2011: https://mobileread.com/forums/showthread.php?t=128076‚Ä¶). Browsers can't read zipped HTML; I kept extracting .htmlz files and fixing styling issues like the awful `text-align: justify`, all of which unbook now handles. https://i.imgur.com/eeigZJx.jpg","thread_hash":"0xb1460bc592daf85c2e7a2c6ffd5b59222f0e837fe0bc3c98519a26a9aa6e0e09","hash":"0x693b1906c925fc01bcf612cff8c9aa4c0177c639ed7dfc8c3e99af2b6238f93e","likes":0,"replies":1,"recasts":0},{"text":"nixpkgs/Nix is another way to do this because you can override the version and hash in a package definition and Nix will rebuild everything as needed","thread_hash":"0xd8b6cefeb5969eecfeb439e7d888cdf011462eea5c415054c28ad6d5e11c4e35","hash":"0xa2e1f00c9dfb4a278fe35267b5ddca2e44d77a50cc0be989f274f2a56ec9682c","likes":0,"replies":0,"recasts":0},{"text":"The inlining of images was inspired by SingleFile, which convinced me that long data URIs and large HTML files are generally no problem. The rewriting of image URLs to data: URIs is handled by Cloudflare's very helpful lol-html library: https://github.com/cloudflare/lol-html","thread_hash":"0xb1460bc592daf85c2e7a2c6ffd5b59222f0e837fe0bc3c98519a26a9aa6e0e09","hash":"0xbb20fa73ec731b0168238e0db8c620c3ed85e591188f15a5c0669cfac5a44e1b","likes":0,"replies":0,"recasts":0},{"text":"gist.github.com/ivan/caea21522a563d1413a32b5a95f54638 a combined list of filters that I put into uBlock Origin's 'My filters' to fix website typography problems and other annoyances","thread_hash":"0xda3429434500637f3128ec1a9fed90bd70f646c5ca4ea9aa75c14ad4b4e43e55","hash":"0xda3429434500637f3128ec1a9fed90bd70f646c5ca4ea9aa75c14ad4b4e43e55","likes":0,"replies":0,"recasts":0},{"text":"https://github.com/ludios/useful-bookmarklets a collection of bookmarklets I use frequently: kill sticky, replace all font-family, override all colors, inject width=device-width, invert all images, set a background-color for images with a transparent background\n\n(bookmarklets can indeed be used on mobile too.)","thread_hash":"0x07928ba95d0259fbc2eca0d652de0070896b94b41c47fe30275cf8cf33890ce2","hash":"0x07928ba95d0259fbc2eca0d652de0070896b94b41c47fe30275cf8cf33890ce2","likes":0,"replies":0,"recasts":0}]},"first_cast_view":{"cast":{"fid":"6168","text":"Currently working on a program to convert ebooks to a single HTML file, because I really prefer to use my browser and have normal scroll behavior. base64-encoding all the images like SingleFile was pretty easy; the harder part is fixing all the parts of Calibre‚Äôs CSS that impair reading. https://i.imgur.com/HdWpAsD.jpg","published_at":"2022-11-27T03:24:04.883Z","hash":"0x5fb31440f7a81bb4afc5146bce7ea6bbb2ea870ef162772c8298f6f05d21bcfd"}},"top_domains_view":{"top_domains":[{"domain":"github.com","count":2},{"domain":"gist.github.com","count":1},{"domain":"mobileread.com","count":1},{"domain":"unbook.ludios.org","count":1}]},"responded_by_view":{"top_replies":[]},"